srcinfo.typesrc: Recorded subdivision plats from Travis County
srcinfo.srccontr: Subdivision plats show the orientation of the lots and ROW which are recorded with the County. Addresses are then assigned based upon the county-wide addressing grid.
Site Plans provide information on how commercial lots are accessed. Addresses are then assigned based on access to the property.
Aerials are images which are rectified to survey data.
Enlarged plat maps called "sections" were used to address the original downtown area. They have been kept for historical purposes.
Produced by the Travis County Appraisal District, delineating the property lines of every legal parcel in the county.

dataqual.complete: Error can be introduced by: digitizing methods, source material, generalization, symbol interpretation, the specifications of aerial photography, aerotriangulation technique, ground control reliability, photogrammetric characteristics, scribing precision, resolution, processing algorithms and printing limitations.
dataqual.logic: QA/QC measures include checking for: duplicate addresses, 0 Place ID's, addresses outside of segment range, address points which do not match Street Name in Segment FC, addresses with incorrect jurisdiction, addresses on wrong side of street, active addresses in AMANDA that are not in GIS (and vice versa), address points with exact same coordinates.
